  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bwindi Community Hospital  Project - live at Birth</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The maternal and child death rates in Uganda remain high. Less than half of deliveries take place with the help of a skilled health worker. This project aims to improve survival rates of mothers and their children in a poor, remote area in the South West of Uganda. It will increase access to maternal and child healthcare through community outreach and the introduction of an innovative health insurance scheme that promotes solidarity and collective action within communities. As a result, maternal and child death rates will be reduced, community members will have a greater awareness of the importance of family planning and there will be better access to maternal and child health services for the poorest people.</narrative>
  </description>
